-59th Omni Monk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ucyjax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cyjax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiny Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#660000>(8/31/01 9:22:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=201.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: wepon Vs Fists</span><hr size=1> Its no rumor Gordee.  A melee weapon, any weapon from what I understand, can enhance your MA hth fighting.  All you need is a MA skill of higher than aroun 125-150 I believe.  Maybe it was 100, I don't know.  Anyway, then, when you equip your weapon and attack, you both punch and swing the weap.<br>
<br>
I know this for a fact, as I do it every time I log on.  I can tell I am hitting with both because around the time that my weapon delay comes around, sometimes I hit for lower damage, and hear a SLASH sound, and every time my punch delay comes around, when I hit I hear a CRUNCH sound, and hit for my normal punch amounts.  Oh, and when I scroll out to watch myself fight, sure enough my weapon is swinging, and my fist protrudes in a punch when my punch comes up.<br>
<br>
Only thing you have to be careful for is the weapon bug.  Sometimes, when equiping or unequiping your weapon, a bug rears its ugly head that doesn't allow you to hit with your fists, or with your weapon, or both.  Its easy to tell when you are used to fighting with both.  Others people on this board have solutions to that bug, but I can't remember them now.  I always just unequip my weap, and zone out and back in to clear it.  Works for me.<br>
<br>
-Cyjax <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=201.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showNextMessage?topicID=201.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=201.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.emailToFriend?topicID=201.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.threadControl?topicID=201.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=201.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=201.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub83.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thepunchingbag74708frm4">House Rules<option value="thepunchingbag74708frm1">Main Dojo<option value="thepunchingbag74708frm2">All About Gear<option value="thepunchingbag74708frm6">Raw Data<option value="thepunchingbag74708frm10">Pol